      • ExtendedMBeanServer

        public ExtendedMBeanServer(MBeanServer mbeanServer,
                           boolean autoQuote,
                           boolean supportHierarchy,
                           boolean supportServerSideMBeanInfoCompression)
        Constructor.
        Parameters:
        mbeanServer - the underlying MBean server to use
        autoQuote - if true, this MBean server will automatically quote key property values in object names
        supportHierarchy - whether hierarchy support should be enabled. Turning it off when it is not needed improves performance
        supportServerSideMBeanInfoCompression - whether server-side MBeanInfo compression should be supported, as per IMBeanInfoCompression

    • Method Detail

      • addNotificationListenerSafe

        public void addNotificationListenerSafe(ObjectName objectName,
                                        NotificationListener notificationListener,
                                        NotificationFilter notificationFilter,
                                        Object handback)
        Description copied from interface: IExtendedMBeanServer
        Utility routine for adding a notification listener to an MBean without having to catch any JMX-related exception. Such exceptions are reported as {IllegalStateException}s.
        Specified by:
        addNotificationListenerSafe in interface IExtendedMBeanServer
        Parameters:
        objectName - The name of the MBean on which the listener should be added
        notificationListener - The listener object which will handle the notifications emitted by the registered MBean
        notificationFilter - The filter object. If filter is null, no filtering will be performed before handling notifications
        handback - The context to be sent to the listener when a notification is emitted
        See Also:
        MBeanServer.addNotificationListener(javax.management.ObjectName, javax.management.NotificationListener, javax.management.NotificationFilter, java.lang.Object)

      • getDescendants

        public HashSet<ObjectName> getDescendants(ObjectName objectName)
        Description copied from interface: IExtendedMBeanServer
        Given an object name, retrieves the set of object names representing all descendants of this MBean currently registered in the MBean server, as per the MA's hierarchical naming scheme.
        Specified by:
        getDescendants in interface IExtendedMBeanServer
        Parameters:
        objectName - the ObjectName of an MBean
        Returns:
        a HashSet, containing all the descendants of the MBean registered under name objectName as per the MA's hierarchical naming scheme. This set will be empty in the case where no MBean is currently registered under name objectName or if this Mbean has got no descendant.

      • quote

        protected ObjectName quote(ObjectName objectName)
        Quotes the given object name if auto-quoting is turned on.
        Parameters:
        objectName - the objectName to quote
        Returns:
        • null if objectName is null
        • objectName if auto-quoting is turned off or if objectName is the name of the MBeanServerDelegate
        • the quoted version of objectName if auto-quoting is turned on
